{"lemma": "رُبَّ", "slug": "رُبَّ", "root": "ر.ب.ب", "root_slug": "ر-ب-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ر-ب-ب", "pos": "PART", "pos_camel": "part", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "رُبَّ", "root": "ربو", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 7, "pos_tags": ["adj", "adv", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 19}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n14369"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "many a", "fa": "بسیار", "ur": "بہت سے", "tr": "birçok", "id": "banyak", "bn": "অনেক", "es": "muchos", "fr": "beaucoup", "de": "mancher", "ru": "многие", "zh": "许多"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be master, to be lord"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to have possession, to gather, to control"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to have authority over, to govern"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to impact, to comprise, to contain"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to collect, to congregate"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to grow, to increase, to become greater"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to bring up, to raise (a child)"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "master, lord, king, sovereign, potentate", "examples": [{"text": "رَبُّ الدَّار", "english": "master of the house"}, {"text": "رَبُّ الْعَائِلَة", "english": "paterfamilias"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "Lord, an epithet of God", "examples": [{"text": "اَللهُ رَبُّ الْعَالَمِين", "english": "God is Lord of the Worlds"}, {"text": "الرَّبّ", "english": "the LORD"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "god, deity", "examples": [{"text": "يَا صَاحِبَيِ السِّجْنِ أَأَرْبَابٌ مُّتَفَرِّقُونَ خَيْرٌ أَمِ اللّٰهُ الْوَاحِدُ الْقَهَّارُ", "english": "[Joseph said:] \"O my two companions of the prison! Are many different deities better than God the One [Who is the Source of all things], the Overpowering?\""}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "leader, chief, head", "examples": [{"text": "رَبُّ بَحْرِيّ", "english": "seaman (naval rank)"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "owner, proprietor"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "one possessed of, one endowed with"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "having to do with"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of رَبَّ (rabba) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "thickened fruit juice, thickened juice"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "mash, pulp"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "many", "examples": [{"text": "رُبَّ رَجُلٍ", "english": "many a man"}, {"text": "رُبَّ مَرَّةٍ", "english": "many a time"}]}, {"pos": "adv", "gloss": "likely, perhaps, mayhap, potentially"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From Proto-Semitic *rabb-."}, "ipa": ["/rab.ba/", "/rabb/", "/rubb/", "/rub.ba/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n14369", "headword_ar": "رُبَّ", "root": "rb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "is a word of which there are seventy dial. vars., all mentioned by Zekereeyà El-Ansáree in his great Expos. of the “ Munferijeh, ” but only eighteen of which are mentioned in the K, including some that are formed with the affix"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "t", "text_ar": "ت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", some with the affix"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and some with both these affixes together; as follows: (TA:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~a", "text_ar": "رُبَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, Msb, Mughnee, K, &c.) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~a", "text_ar": "رَبَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M, Mughnee, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~u", "text_ar": "رُبُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mughnee,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruba", "text_ar": "رُبَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, Mughnee, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raba", "text_ar": "رَبَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M, Mughnee, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rubu", "text_ar": "رُبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rubo", "text_ar": "رُبْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mughnee, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rabo", "text_ar": "رَبْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Mughnee;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~ata", "text_ar": "رُبَّتَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, Msb, Mughnee, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~ata", "text_ar": "رَبَّتَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, Mughnee, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~uta", "text_ar": "رُبُّتَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~atu", "text_ar": "رُبَّتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~atu", "text_ar": "رَبَّتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~utu", "text_ar": "رُبُّتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~ati", "text_ar": "رُبَّتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~ati", "text_ar": "رَبَّتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~uti", "text_ar": "رُبُّتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~ut", "text_ar": "رَبُّت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA)"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1004}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~ato", "text_ar": "رُبَّتْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~ato", "text_ar": "رَبَّتْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mughnee) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rub~uto", "text_ar": "رُبُّتْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rubata", "text_ar": "رُبَتَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, Mughnee, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rabata", "text_ar": "رَبَتَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mughnee, K) and"}, {"kin